        <h2>Celebrity Lash Myths vs. Reality</h2>

        <h3>Myth: Celebrities Get Lash Extensions Redone Weekly</h3>
        <p><strong>Reality:</strong> Most celebrities get fills every 2-3 weeks, just like everyone else. They just have glam teams for touch-ups before major events.</p>

        <h3>Myth: Red Carpet Lashes Are Always Extensions</h3>
        <p><strong>Reality:</strong> Many celebrities combine lash extensions with strip lashes for extra drama at events, then remove the strips after.</p>

        <h3>Myth: Celebrity Lashes Are Expensive Special Products</h3>
        <p><strong>Reality:</strong> Celebrities use the same high-quality synthetic lashes available at professional salons like ours. The difference is in the artist's skill.</p>

        <h3>Myth: You Need a Ton of Maintenance</h3>
        <p><strong>Reality:</strong> Celebrity lash artists recommend the same aftercare we do: gentle cleansing, no oil-based products, and regular fills.</p>

